[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering JUnit test structure**\n\nI’m exploring whether we can make a package-private static class inside a test class. JUnit can discover static nested classes, but they need to be annotated with @ClassTemplate and @ExtendWith to be executed as separate tests. Is it okay for a class to have no tests? Maybe a class template without @Test could cause issues. It seems better to provide at least a simple @Test in the nested class template just to be safe.\n\n**Considering file paths and class sources**\n\nI’m thinking about how to handle file paths effectively. It seems like using `Path.of(\"build\", \"test-class-scanner-generated\", \"sources\")` could work, without needing to create files. Maybe I should consider if there’s a way to use a builder that requires specific values or even if using `static final` could help. Also, I need to check if `ClassSource` could give me the classpath roots I need.\n\n**Inspecting test reports**\n\nI need to take a closer look at the native test reports for the existing tests. This will give me a better understanding of how they're performing and where any adjustments might be necessary. It’s essential to evaluate the results thoroughly so I can consider any potential improvements or fixes. Keeping track of these details helps ensure that everything is running smoothly and effectively. Let’s see what insights we can gather from the reports!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0fd3d89339e1819a016a299b6800c88197a2437fed836a70e3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKZuH4E6L6e1K3hT03CEYvfE-rqY88o5QGAECEHWgYUczy8KFzRxjDQGoTqmZRWDYTnCLuQeJkC1CYB4XWjdqp3ued7EUrjgqwJALTtq_TI-njJgPaOHZvhrQTp5YgBGYQQcBOgkbvHXQdLTrKLzPnH_VZHmbCHipWb2d8IxqKvh-KIMAPkHVMWbMkss2xpoNwjTvxryHBDnBphv7k_wiIQbvuEhiDSCSgfoR1WbYdQNBWMRFcvbu3kYkWKp2OWxIVh4Lxfe48F5jQdKCuse9UH5C_to22bu585OhqnlPSQnlzRTdvIU6JRDQQ6ShGg7iAxFSFgLe3wv