pe": "text", "text": "Fixed the compilation failure by adding the required JUnit 6 dependencies for the `@ClassTemplate` API used by `TestClassScannerTest`.\n\nUpdated:\n- `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build.gradle`\n\nAdded:\n```groovy\ntestImplementation 'org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:6.0.0'\ntestImplementation 'org.junit.platform:junit-platform-launcher:6.0.0'\ntestRuntimeOnly 'org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-engine:6.0.0'\n```\n\nReason:\n- `org.junit.jupiter.api.ClassTemplate`\n- `ClassTemplateInvocationContext`\n- `ClassTemplateInvocationContextProvider`\n\nare JUnit Jupiter 6 APIs and were not available on the existing test classpath. The scanner behavior being covered is specifically Spring Test’s JUnit class-template expansion path, so adding the matching JUnit dependency is the appropriate fix rather than stubbing or bypassing the API.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0fd3d89339e1819a016a299c59cf548197ac88e8461577eea9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 25716, "output": 716, "cacheRead": 10752, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37184, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781111880044, "responseId": "resp_0fd3d89339e1819a016a299c48f5348197842efd081fa33cbc"}}
